crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects a suspicious ELF binary with UPX compression
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a variant of the Mozi botnet, specifically targeting MIPS-based IoT devices and routers. It demonstrates extensive malicious capabilities including automated exploitation of vulnerabilities in network devices (targeting Huawei, Realtek SDK, and GPON routers), persistence through the modification of system initialization scripts (/etc/rc.local and /etc/init.d/S95baby.sh), and firewall manipulation via iptables to allow bot communication. It utilizes SSDP/UPnP for NAT traversal and port mapping to ensure external connectivity. The binary interacts with system watchdogs to prevent reboots and contains multiple hardcoded URLs for downloading additional Mozi components (e.g., Mozi.m, Mozi.a, Mozi.7) and command injection templates.
